name: Solar Flare
description:
CHROMACELL #2 - by Rose Croft

Macrophotograph of Original Hand Painted Artwork -  Acrylic and Gesso on paper. 

This artwork is part of a series of hexagonal sections named "Chromacells."  They are cut from large layered abstract paintings that are made specifically to be destroyed.  
Each Chromacell is a consequence of this destructive process and represents a single moment of creation -  reflecting the cyclical nature of life. 

For this reason Chromacells are always 1/1s.
